Malam Abubakar Nuhu Fikpo has been nominated as the acting Director-General of the National Directorate of Employment (NDE).  He was nominated by President Muhammadu Buhari contrary to the position of the Senate which on December 10, 2020, according to a report by Punch. The Senate had urged Buhari to rescind the presidential directive sacking Dr. Nasiru Argungu, as the NDE DG. A statement by the president’s Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Malam Garba Shehu, in Abuja on Monday, said the president’s decision had already been conveyed to the Minister of State, Labour and Employment, Mr Festus Keyamo. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that President Buhari had on Dec. 9, 2020, relieved the former DG of the agency, Nasiru Ladan Argungu, of his appointment. According to Shehu, the directive on the sack of NDE DG was given on Dec. 4, 2020, but took effect from Dec. 7, 2020. Source By Awayi Kuje Lafia - The National Directorate of Employment (NDE) says over 900,000 unemployed Nigerians have been trained and empowered in the last two years to enable them become self reliant and contribute their quota to national development. Dr  Nasiru Ladan-Argungu, the NDE Director General, said this on Thursday… July 12, 2019 In "News" Jalingo - To meet the demands of unemployed Nigerians, the National Directorate of Employment (NDE) on Monday empowered 300 women and youths with N10,000 each in Taraba. The event took place in Jalingo at the NUT Secretariat, when the persons earlier trained in vocational skills, cosmetology and Basic Business Training… February 11, 2019 In "Business" President Muhammadu Buhari has given Minister of State for Labour and Employment, Festus Keyamo, the go-ahead with the plan to recruit 774, 000 under the Special Public Works Progamme (SPW). Keyamo confirmed the development to The Nation on Wednesday in Abuja. The Minister said he has the instructions of President… July 14, 2020 In "News"